CatDescriptText: Two cars have collided in downtown Pittsburgh in front of Guentert's Bakery and a Laundromat.  One man checks the damage on the right hand car, a 1950 Buick Special Deluxe Four-door sedan.  On the left, three men and a woman stand beside a 1955 Oldsmobile Super 88 Holiday four-door hardtop.  In the background, Loft's Candy store and a partially constructed building are visible.  A distant street sign in front of the construction site may read "Liberty Ave."
TitMainTitle: Men, including one with cane, observing wreck with Oldsmobile and Buick cars in front of Guentert's Bakery near Loft's Candy, Downtown
